Where I grew up in Australia it never snows, it wasn't until I was 21 that I first saw snow at Perisher mountain on the east coast of Australia. I was over that way for a work trip, we decided to spend the last day traveling 4 hours so we could snowboard for 1. I had no idea what I was doing, my mate told me to point the board down the mountain and figure it out, it was terrifying, it was amazing, I knew I needed more.

Later that year that same mate, another colleague (Barker), and several other people I barely knew (Nixon and Jones) took a trip to Hakuba Japan, the first night we arrived we went snowboarding. Not only did I not know what I was doing, I nearly impaled myself on safety railing as I fell down the mountain screaming "I don't know how to stop".

