Not long after this vacation my life was turned upside down and I moved to New York, following my now good mate Barker. One of the justifications of this move was that I would be able to experience a lot more snow in America, in fact before I left my soon-to-be supervisor emailed me to let me know of a snowboarding trip she was organizing. I signed up immediately awaited patiently my first trip to a U.S. resort.

That first day-trip was incredible, no longer did I have to take an international flight to access a good resort, instead I could leave the city at 4am and take a 5 hour bus trip up to the Killington Mountain. Again I built bonds with people that I barely knew and would later become good friends, and Barker and I continued to chase each other down the mountain, improving, falling, and laughing all the day.

