In November 2012 we went up to Killington again, it was a little early in the season but we were too excited to let any more time pass before we played in the snow again. I was anxious to try out my new board and excited to hang out with my friends, at the beginning of the first run though I lagged behind to help someone, which meant I then had to scramble to find everyone again.

Finally the sport caught up with me, and as I rushed down the mountain to find my group I took a blind turn, skid to avoid the tourists blocking the run, and threw my wrist down to break my fall. I felt the pain immediately in my wrist, even now as I write this 3 years later I can remember the pain, followed by the dread as I pulled my glove off to watch my hand fall away from my arm.

